# Project context

1. **Design system** — Follow `DESIGN.md` at the repo root for colors, typography, borders, and component language. **`app/globals.css`** defines **dark default + light inversion** (`data-theme`); use semantic Tailwind tokens (`bg-canvas`, `text-fg`, `border-border`, `outline-accent`, surfaces, etc.—see DESIGN.md §2) instead of hardcoded `#`/`rgba` so both themes stay in sync.

2. **React / Next.js** — Apply guidance from `.agents/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/` (rule files and `SKILL.md`) when writing, reviewing, or refactoring React and Next.js code: avoid request waterfalls, optimize bundles and server/client data flow, and keep renders efficient as described there.
